com.emc.ecs.nfsclient.mount

Class MountResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.emc.ecs.nfsclient.rpc.RpcResponse
      • com.emc.ecs.nfsclient.mount.MountResponse

  • public class MountResponse
extends RpcResponse
    Representation of a Mount response, as specified by RFC 1813 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1813).

    Procedure MNT maps a pathname on the server to a file handle.

      • MountResponse

        public MountResponse(int nfsVersion)
        Creates the response, as specified by RFC 1813 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1813).

        Procedure MNT maps a pathname on the server to a file handle.

        Parameters:
        nfsVersion - The NFS version number. This is ignored for now, as only NFSv3 is supported, but is included to allow future support for other versions.

      • getMountStatus

        public int getMountStatus()
        Returns:
        A status indicator, expected to have one of the MountStatus values as below.
        • MNT3_OK = 0 (no error)
        • MNT3ERR_PERM = 1 (Not owner)
        • MNT3ERR_NOENT = 2 (No such file or directory)
        • MNT3ERR_IO = 5 (I/O error)
        • MNT3ERR_ACCES = 13 (Permission denied)
        • MNT3ERR_NOTDIR = 20 (Not a directory)
        • MNT3ERR_INVAL = 22 (Invalid argument)
        • MNT3ERR_NAMETOOLONG = 63 (Filename too long)
        • MNT3ERR_NOTSUPP = 10004 (Operation not supported)
        • MNT3ERR_SERVERFAULT = 10006 (A failure on the server)

      • getRootFileHandle

        public byte[] getRootFileHandle()
        Returns:
        The file handle for the exported directory.

      • getAuthenticationFlavors

        public int[] getAuthenticationFlavors()
        Returns:
        The array of supported authentication flavors, as defined in RFC 1831 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1831).
